Package.Name: CSV
Package.Description: This plugin package contains a result listener that allows for results to be output in a CSV format. CSV is a common data exchange format that is widely supported by consumer, business, and scientific applications. It is basically plain text saved in a tabular format and the settings let you configure which separator to use: comma, semicolon or tabular. ReleasedKeysight Technologies

Package.Name: SQLite and PostgreSQL
Package.Description:
This package contains two result listeners that make it possible to connect to an SQLite or PostgreSQL database. SQLite is a self-contained, high-reliability, embedded SQL database that is represented by a single file (SqliteDatabase.TapResults) in the installation directory. For larger data sets or remote collection and sharing of data, a more standard database like PostgreSQL is recommended. The PostgreSQL plugin lets you specify a connection to a local or remote PostgreSQL database server (PostgreSQL is free and open source).
Note that the Run Explorer and Results Viewer applications leverage the SQLite or PostgreSQL plugins to data mine and visualize the measurement data. ReleasedKeysight Technologies

Package.Name: Editor CE
Package.Description: This is the Community Edition (CE) of the Test Plan Editor. It is a graphical user interface (GUI) that consists of a set of user panels that make it possible to quickly construct test plans consisting of multiple test steps. Furthermore, it allows the assignment of resources such as DUTs and instruments as well as result storage. It lets you control test plan execution, monitor progress and log output. Update required to use after 5/21 2020. ReleasedKeysight Technologies

Package.Name: Results Viewer CE
Package.Description: The Results Viewer brings the power of relational databases to result visualization, empowering your test plan development with a consistent way of viewing data across multiple stages of your engineering process. Each time a test plan is executed the results can be stored in a database (SQLite, PostgreSQL,.. ) which can be graphed and visualized using the Results Viewer. Also provided is the test plan Run Explorer to help manage test plan data, recall old test plans, merge and compare test log timings and more. Update required to use after 5/21 2020. ReleasedKeysight Technologies
